(TTFS) Wilshire Buyback ETF


Overview


How TTFS Works
The AdvisorShares Wilshire Buyback ETF (NYSE Arca: TTFS) seeks to generate long-term capital appreciation. TTFS is sub-advised by Wilshire Associates Incorporated, through its Wilshire Funds Management division (“Portfolio Manager”). The Fund seeks to achieve this objective by investing in stocks with liquidity and fundamental characteristics that are historically associated with superior long-term performance. Stock selection for TTFS is based on extensive historical research from Wilshire Associates, a leading independent institutional firm with a long-standing reputation of innovation.


